args:
Shunned by the villagers, Vania falls into a deep
funk. But when word arrives that more blood-
drained animals have turned up, she races from
the Halidom to protect the children she still
considers her dear friends.
Oh, Vania. This is fortuitous. We're off to\npick some fruit. Would you care to join us?
Yeah! I've got this secret spot where\nthe most AMAZING apples grow!
...but I think I'll pass.\nI'm not really feeling it today.
She's taking it pretty hard, huh?
Can you blame her? She whacked that\nfiend to help the villagers and clear her\nname, and all it did was scare them away.
Even I had no idea a vampire's powers\nwere quite so impressive. I can't entirely\nblame the villagers for their response...
But still, I feel awful for her! There's gotta\nbe something we can do to help... Right?
That may prove difficult. Once it takes\nroot, fear is a difficult emotion to dispel.
...Malinda, do you think there's any way\nfor vampires and humans to get along?
To man's eyes, vampires are a predator.\nI believe it unlikely that a being could\nbefriend that which threatens its survival.
But I don't even EAT people!
Fruit tastes way better anyway.\nDon't you think?
I have not eaten either, so I fear\nI lack any basis for comparison.
Huh? What are you talking about?\nYou love fruit.
You always say that's how you got so\nplump, because you can't stop once you\nget started on—wait a minute.
But you're NOT plump. Weird...\nWhy would I think you said that?
The village children haven't been seen\nsince last night.
You were friends with them, weren't you?\nAny ideas where they might have gone?
They may be in the forest.\nThey spoke of a secret place there.
Oh! That could be it, yeah. They said they\nwere gonna show it to me. That I'd really\nlike it.
The forest... We need to be swift if we're\nto find them before anything happens.
More livestock were killed last night.\nThey were...drained of their blood.
What?! No way! I took care of—
There must have been more than one\nculprit.
Judging from the traces left behind, the\nfiends' nest is in that forest. It isn't safe\nfor the children to be there.
Then... Ummm, I'll be right back!
She practically ZOOMED outta here,\nguys. What do we do?
We go after her. We need to find those\nchildren as soon as possible.
...Not here, either. Nor have I seen any\nsign of Vania. I hope someone has found\nthe children by now.
Hark, prince vexed by fate's machinations.

I am a war-god: he who has crossed
countless worlds on orders from the
keeper of fate and causality to preserve
time's order.
My name is the wind, my form the whorl,\nmy power the mighty storm. I am the mad\ncyclone... Grimnir!
Grimnir? Wait, I've heard this voice before.
Awww, you remembered me?! Oh, WHEW.\nI was worried you'd think it was all just a\nDREAM and FORGET and then...
ACK! Rewind, cut that last bit!\nYou heard nothing! *ahem*\nI am come with a warning, O Prince.
About what? No, wait. First, where ARE\nyou? Would you mind showing yourself?
Sadly, this I cannot do. My body resides in\nthe narrow gap 'twixt fate and fate and\n'tween world and world.
To stand before you in the flesh, I would\nneed slip the stubborn strictures of time\nitself.
Oof, did that one not get across? I mean\nit's gonna take me a hot minute to get\nthere.
So, y'know, try to stay safe 'til then, okay?
Yeah, you know the guy... Right? Tall,\ndark, and time-warpy? Artificial dragon?
Yes, I've had the displeasure... But I—
Vanquished him? Yeah, that did definitely\nhappen, but hey, time dragons! *ahem*\nYou well know him for a persistent foe.
What's more, he was wrought by man for\nwicked purpose. Perhaps so too was he\nrestored by human hands.
Then he's returned to life? But...\nWho ARE you? How do you know all this?
We are locked in a fated slap-fight... Er,\nI guess it's more of a cosmic squabble?\nUgh, this isn't sounding as cool as it is.
You are losing me more with every breath.
Look, it's a long story, okay?\nWe don't have time to get into it here.
Just watch your back, and DON'T listen to\nanything he says!
And above all, you must protect the—
The...? He cut out again. Grimnir? Are\nyou still there?! What am I to protect?
...It's no use. I can't hear anything.
But is Chronos truly returned?\nThen it must be...
There you are, {player_name}.\nI come to you with an urgent request.
No... Sorry, everything is fine. It's rare to\nhear you ask for help. What's happened?
Vania has found both the fiends and the\nvillage children.
I know not the specifics, but it seems she\ncame across them just as the children\nwere being attacked by multiple fiends.
She moved to strike them down, but their\nnumbers are many, and she is struggling\nto face them while protecting the children.
We must hasten to help her.\nShe sent me here to enlist your aid.
All right. Where are they?\nCan you lead us there?
Just watch your back, and DON'T listen to\nanything he says!
(This ＂Malinda＂—it has to be Chronos.\nIs it safe to follow him here?)
(Though it's not as if I've any real reason\nto trust Grimnir's words, either...)
No, nothing. Let's go.\nVania needs us!
